Claudia Martins was suffering from a 'pathological denial of pregnancy' She was cleared of murder but convicted of manslaughter on the grounds of diminished responsibility . 
  Court heard she suffocated her newborn baby daughter by stuffing toilet paper down her throat and hiding the infant's body in a suitcase . 
  Martins wept as she was sentenced to a two year community order . 
  Judge accepted she had a 'momentary abnormality of mental functioning'